Preparing for concerts, individual vocal training, basics of vocal techniques, performing publically, participating in different music projects with orchestras, leading soloists etc., participating in events connected to the University of Tartu.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To enable students of the University of Tartu to participate in male voice choir practice.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successfully completing the course students: - have experience in singing in a male voice choir; - can interpret choir music through the classics of Estonian and Western European choir music; - are familiar with elementary music theory and have basic knowledge about music; - have acquired essential knowledge about the basics of vocal techniques.
